Bridges -- Tennessee -- Memphis
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Memphis Bridge (now called the Frisco Bridge) was one of the longest railroad bridges in the world when it opened on March 12, 1892. Designed by George S. Morison, the bridge helped transform Memphis into a distribution center for freight businesses.
